    <div class="odd">
        <h3>Meal List</h3>
        <p>
            This project was a foray into search algorithms and data storage. The goal of this project was to create a
            way to search for meals based on name or ingredient in a form that could be adapted to a website or a
            different database with minimal changes. I made the choice to handle most user interaction in a single
            class, and the entirety of the database interaction in its own class. The purpose of the database
            interaction being entirely separate and abstracted was to allow for me to change the database from a CSV
            file to a proper SQL database and only have to change a single file. The search algorithm had room for
            improvement, notably the ability to search for multiple ingredients at once, though I feel it was a good way
            to close off the intro to Java class. I learned a lot about abstracting outside interaction in a way that
            minimizes the code that needs to change to accommodate the new database.
        </p>
