        <h3>RoboCode</h3>
        <p>
            RoboCode is a coding challenge where you compete with other people to have the most powerful robot. I knew
            that the best robot would probably be the simplest, so I decided to spend the majority of my time working to
            figure out what makes for the most effective robot. I determined that the most effective robot was one that
            just spins and avoids being hit. Since most robots will fire until they run out of energy and blow
            themselves up, dodging their shots while dealing with whatever damage they managed to achieve was a strategy
            that consistently placed me in the top 3. This was an exercise in analysis and it was useful to learn how
            about how to read documentation for a Java class.
        </p>
