        <h3>Application Security Paper</h3>
        <p>
            This paper entailed learning about a virus and what could have been done to prevent the infection. I had
            heard about a virus called StuxNet before, and decided that was a good virus to choose. Stuxnet ended up
            being a cyberweapon used against Iranian nuclear enrichment facilities, with multiple countries aiding in
            the development. I decided that the only way this weapon could have been avoided was to not be an enemy of a
            rich nation who dislikes your industry, since everything I read about the targeting of the enrichment plant
            said that the virus was going to get in no matter what. The other smaller conclusion was to avoid plugging
            random usb drives into your computer, as that was the primary method of transmission for Stuxnet and it
            gives implicit trust to the drive. The research and writing of the paper went smoothly enough, and the resulting
            presentation was a lot of fun. I learned a lot about how sophisticated viruses can get, and just how
            important cyber security is for every organization.
        </p>
